news.title: China's Kaisa Group halts trading as property woes grow
news.para: For now, all eyes are on a key Saturday deadline for Evergrande to pay an $82.5 million coupon on a bond. The firm missed the initial payment last month but was given a 30-day grace period. It has stumped up for two others in recent weeks.

news.title: Omaxe lease out 10.5 lakh sq ft space between Apr-Oct 2021
news.para: In Greater Noida, the company has leased 6.77 lakh sq ft, 2.95 lakh sq ft in Lucknow, 58,222 sq ft in Faridabad, and 20,000 sq ft in Amritsar.

news.title: Chinese developers' shares, bonds stumble again
news.para: In early trade in Hong Kong, a sub-index tracking the mainland property sector fell more than 2%, deepening its losses in the past two weeks to nearly 20%. An index of real estate A-shares fell more than 1.6% against a 0.25% drop in the broader blue-chip index.

news.title: China: Kaisa Group's unit misses payment, debt worries mount
news.para: Kaisa's troubles come amid concerns about a deepening liquidity crisis in the Chinese property sector, with a string of offshore debt defaults, credit rating downgrades, and sell offs in the developers' shares and bonds in recent weeks.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board got Rs 16 crore via online transactions in 22 months
news.para: Besides, the board had received over Rs one crore through online transactions in the months of February Rs 1.32 crore; March Rs 1.32 crore; May Rs 1.51 crore; July Rs 1.02 crore and August Rs 1.94 crore.

news.title: Gujarat: Ceramic tile prices up 10% after gas price revision
news.para: "Tile prices have been increased by 10% with effect from November 1. The prices have been revised thrice in the past three months due to the increased prices of natural gas and other fuels," said Mukesh Kundariya, president, vitrified tiles division, MCA.

news.title: Mumbai: 19 tenants of Gajanan Colony get redeveloped flats after seven years
news.para: The court had heard a petition by 19 out of 120 tenants of the Gajanan Colony, which comprised four buildings, at Eksar Pahadi. They had vacated their homes in 2014, and though the redeveloped building was ready & OC had been granted in February 2021, Earth Graphics did not hand over possession.

news.title: Can slum resettlement policy make eviction less painful?
news.para: Tamil Nadu has drawn up its first draft resettlement and rehabilitation policy. While this is a significant step, the draft policy in its present form leaves much room for improvement.

news.title: Bengaluru: BDA to fast-track applications from revenue site owners in Dr Shivaram Karanth layout
news.para: The layout, which is spread across 17 villages between Doddaballapura and Hesaraghatta, is likely to accommodate 22,000 sites of various dimensions

news.title: Kerala to ramp up cement production in PSUs to bring down construction cost
news.para: Responding to a calling attention motion by Sunny Joseph MLA, the minister said the state is manufacturing only 10% of the cement required here and 90% of the cement market of the state is being controlled by private companies outside the state.

news.title: Kerala government earns Rs 447 crore through land conversion
news.para: ​​As per this, no permission is required for constructing a house of area 120sq m in 10 cents and for constructing a commercial building of 40sq m in five cents of converted land.

news.title: Indore records Rs 842 crore revenue from property sales in Apr-Oct 2021
news.para: District registrar Balkrishna More said, "Property sales have started on a very good note this fiscal. Revenues have gone up and income in the April-October period was up by 72 per cent as against the same period a year ago."

news.title: Nashik civic body to start work on mall projects soon after Diwali
news.para: Municipal commissioner Kailas Jadhav told TOI that the civic body will prepare a detailed project report (DPR) through an agency which will be deployed after Diwali.

news.title: After over 20 years, Goa government nixes lease deed with Indian Resort Hotels
news.para: After a long tussle, the Goa government has terminated the 1997 lease deed with Indian Resort Hotels Ltd — now known as the Indian Hotels Company Ltd (IHCL) — to set-up recreational facilities for tourists on over 3 lakh sqm land at Aguada plateau.

news.title: Punjab CM offers financial aid of Rs 3,100 each for registered construction workers
news.para: ​"The financial grant of Rs 3,100 is a 'shagun' for construction workers and their families on the joyous festival of lights," Charanjit Singh Channi said.
